body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

yosys> read_verilog -sv argument_binding.sv

argument_binding.sv
```
module test(
    input a,
    input b,
    output c
);

    function automatic test();
        input a;
        input b;

        test = a + b;
    endfunction

    assign c = test(.a(a), .b(b));

endmodule

```
## Expected behavior

Equivalent to 

```
module test(
    input a,
    input b,
    output c
);

    function automatic test();
        input a;
        input b;

        test = a + b;
    endfunction

    assign c = test(a, b);

endmodule

```

As per 13.5.4 Argument binding by name (IEEE Std 1800-2012)

## Actual behavior

1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: argument_binding.sv
Parsing SystemVerilog input from `argument_binding.sv' to AST representation.
argument_binding.sv:14: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected '.'

